==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sophomorical
<hw>Soph`o*mor"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to a
sophomore; resembling a sophomore; hence, pretentious; inflated in style
or manner; <as>as, <ex>sophomoric</ex> affectation</as>.</def> <mark>[U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- 2. Poorly informed yet overconfident of one's own knowledge;
asserting incorrect facts based on scant knowledge. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sophora</ent>⟦br⟧
